- cs.DM (Data Mining): The paper deals with the prediction of time series data for graphs, which is a common task in data mining. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a machine learning-based approach for predicting changes in graph structures, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses the application of the proposed approach to various domains, including distributed computing and intelligent tutoring systems, which fall under the purview of computational engineering and science.
